cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes a new methodology for deep reinforcement learning that involves supervised regression and optimization in the non-parameterized proximal policy space. This methodology is applicable to both discrete and continuous action spaces and can handle a variety of proximity constraints. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the development of algorithms and models for learning from data. The paper also involves robotics tasks (Mujoco simulated robotic tasks) and computer vision tasks (Atari video game tasks), which suggest that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with policy optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
